reg_osc<7:4>: xtal_core current trimming 0001: add 20ua 0010: add 40ua 0100: add 80ua 1000: add 160ua 1111: add 300ua

spirit:field.spirit:name: PU_LIMITER
spirit:field.spirit:description: software control of limiter power up/dwon. =0x0 write 0 to this bit has no effect and limiter's power is controled by hardware 0x1= write 1 is to force limiter is powered up

spirit:field.spirit:name: PU
spirit:field.spirit:description: software control of anagrp power up/down =0x0 write 0 to this bit has no effect and anagrp's power is controled by hardware 0x1= write 1 is to force anagrp is powered up

spirit:field.spirit:description: phase interpolator loop control 1 = pi is in the pll loop 0 = pi is out of the pll loop

spirit:field.spirit:name: RESET_SSC
spirit:field.spirit:description: ssc reset, active high both of ssc and frequency offset logic is controlled by this field. make sure this field is 0 when ssc or frequency offset is valid

spirit:field.spirit:name: SSC_CLK_EN
spirit:field.spirit:description: ssc clock enable enables pi output clock for ssc digital logic. set this field to 1 if ssc is enabled.

spirit:field.spirit:name: SSC_MODE
spirit:field.spirit:description: ssc mode selection 0 = center spread 1 = down spread

spirit:field.spirit:name: RESET_PI
spirit:field.spirit:description: external interpolator reset signal 1 = reset 0 = no reset

spirit:field.spirit:name: PI_EN
spirit:field.spirit:description: phase interpolator loop control set to 1 if ssc is enabled 0 = disable phase interpolator 1 = enable phase interpolator

spirit:field.spirit:name: SSC_FREQ_DIV
spirit:field.spirit:description: ssc frequency selection for zero average frequency offset, keep ssc_freq_div[3:0] = 0 and set ssc_freq_div[15:4] to change the ssc frequency.

spirit:field.spirit:name: SSC_RNGE
spirit:field.spirit:description: ssc range select ssc_rnge[10:0] = desired ssc amplitude /(ssc_freq_div[14:0]*2^(-26)) rounding to integer required
